    },
    {
      "id": "yXL8sfuuCUW94vCW7AFlX",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 263,
      "y": 729,
      "width": 808.8394775390625,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 539232123,
      "version": 535,
      "versionNonce": 103565339,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779505587065,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Types oF Agents in ADK:\n\n\n1. LLMAgent -> It uses LLM to do a dynamic reasoning, -> It reads the instruction\nand input / reasons out the plan /  decides which tool to call, when to call/\nProduces the output -> majority of the time we built this kind of Agent\n\n2. Workflow Agents -> Define the workflow(Sequential/ Parallel/ Loop)\n\n The order is determinstic -> no LLM for Orchestration -> Sub-agents willl take \ncare of execution in fixed pattern.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Types oF Agents in ADK:\n\n\n1. LLMAgent -> It uses LLM to do a dynamic reasoning, -> It reads the instruction\nand input / reasons out the plan /  decides which tool to call, when to call/\nProduces the output -> majority of the time we built this kind of Agent\n\n2. Workflow Agents -> Define the workflow(Sequential/ Parallel/ Loop)\n\n The order is determinstic -> no LLM for Orchestration -> Sub-agents willl take \ncare of execution in fixed pattern.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "FjVfthxzT4ILcRfpjCG7z",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 287,
      "y": 1059,
      "width": 625.0394897460938,
      "height": 275,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aJ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1755200795,
      "version": 321,
      "versionNonce": 1987180085,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779505785819,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Features of ADK:\n\n1. Tool Calling -> ADK automatically handles it\n2. Multi-turn memory -> ADK handles it automatically session\n3. Multi - agent routing -> Deterministic and LLM based Routing\n4. Streaming -> Native available\n5. Debugging -> Web UI + Event Inspector\n6. Deployment -> GCP\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Features of ADK:\n\n1. Tool Calling -> ADK automatically handles it\n2. Multi-turn memory -> ADK handles it automatically session\n3. Multi - agent routing -> Deterministic and LLM based Routing\n4. Streaming -> Native available\n5. Debugging -> Web UI + Event Inspector\n6. Deployment -> GCP\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "xrZiWiNJzYNCXECcQGxfU",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 170,
      "y": 1337,
      "width": 735.1995239257812,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1959703477,
      "version": 203,
      "versionNonce": 2127975835,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1779505873198,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "LiteLLM :\n\nGoogle ADK built natively to support Gemini models. But if you want to \nuse Open AI models API then you have LiteLLM  through which it supports\nany Open AI models.\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LiteLLM :\n\nGoogle ADK built natively to support Gemini models. But if you want to \nuse Open AI models API then you have LiteLLM  through which it supports\nany Open AI models.\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "C4PvCB7PJY0h9aOshQK7S",
      "type": "text",
